---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Homelab tinkerer writing about self-hosting, security, and automation."
	pubDate={new Date('June 28 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
			Hi — I'm Andrew. I run a homelab out of a couple of small Proxmox boxes,
			and I like taking things apart to understand how they actually work. This
			site is where I write up the projects I tinker with, mostly so I remember
			how I solved something — and maybe save the next person a few hours.
	</p>

	<p>
			Most of what I do lives somewhere between self-hosting, security, and
			automation: running my own services instead of renting them, poking at
			things to learn how they break, and wiring up small agents to keep an eye
			on it all. Lately I've been getting hands-on with infrastructure-as-code
			and using LLMs as actual tools in my workflow rather than novelties.
	</p>

	<p>
			Expect posts that are equal parts "here's a thing I got working" and
			"here's everything that went wrong first." If something here helps you,
			that's the whole point.
	</p>
</Layout>


